<title>USA: Dayton Superior to buy Symons for $79 mln.</title>
<headline>Dayton Superior to buy Symons for $79 mln.</headline>
<dateline>MIAMISBURG, Ohio 1997-04-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>Dayton Superior Corp said Tuesday that it has signed a letter of intent to acquire Symons Corp for $79 million, in a transaction that would be modestly accretive to earnings per share in 1997.</p>
<p>Symons is a North American manufacturer of prefabricated concrete forming equipment.  The company also manufactures a broad line of concrete accessories and hardware.</p>
<p>Dayton said that Symons had sales of $104.5 million for its fiscal year ended August 31, 1996, which would increase Dayton Superior's revenue base by roughly 80 percent.</p>
